rComments: Professor Kuskey is very smart and knowledgeable about literature, especially British. However, she is pretty rude in class and will call students out for anything she dislikes. Very moody. Incredibly set on race, gender, and queer theory so it eventually gets boring and predictable. On the positive side, she is awesome if you go to office hours.

She's pretty rude to students in class. She will call you out for showing up late or doing anything that isn't giving her attention.  She's super nice and smart though and will do whatever it takes to help you and your grade.  She's pretty dead-set on race & gender theory though. It gets predictable and irritating.  Nice prof, ego aside.

Personally found her personality to be on the aggressive side. Likes to call people out if they are talking or on their phones or walk in late. Once cussed out a skateboarder outside the lecture hall. That was cool. Other than that, her lectures are super interesting and office hours were extremely helpful and she's nicer in person. Go for it.

She needs an attitude check, simply put. She knows how to close read and analyze texts but her manner of encouraging discussion in lecture is very disrespectful. For that reason alone I would recommend to stay away from a course she teaches. The topics were actually interesting to read, but her personality ruins the class. Easy class overall though

Jessica is great. She excepts a lot from her students, so those who do not rise to the occasion may not like her. She is extremely intelligible in Victorian Lit and always gave me good, sound advice when I asked for help. I would definitely recommend taking her class!

Jessica is great. She expects her students to come prepared, and if you don't, she notices. Of course she calls people out for being on their phone or walking in late, we're students and we are wasting her time if we show up unprepared or not interested. She was ALWAYS willing to meet outside of class and gave helpful advice on writing. LOVE her

She is hands down the most immature teacher I have ever had. She still does that thing where she'll call you out for walking in late or using your phone in the middle of lecture. She has no respect for the students and treats us like middle school kids. I don't recommend this professor even though the course is very easy. She is that annoying.

She is amazing. I would love every lit class ever to be taught by her. She is super helpful and makes herself wholly available to students who need/want help. TAKE HER CLASS! She's hilarious and interesting and awesome. I'm really sad that Spring 2014 she's only teaching a lower level class  :(
